title: 820 00165 No VCORE
message:
U1950 had pad 8 missing after liquid in the area. I ran a jumper and replaced the chip. It was working for 2 days but now the fan spins for 10 seconds than stops and restarts and keeps spinning.

Some voltages.

[LIST]
[*]CPUVR_PHASE2 0
[*]PP3V3_SUS 3.3
[*]PM_SLP_SUS_L 3.3
[*]PP3V3_S0 0
[*]PLT_RESET_L 0
[*]ALL_SYS_PWRGD 3.4
[*]PM_BATLOW_L 3.3
[*]CPUVR_PGOOD When I try and check this voltage the machine shuts down.
[/LIST]
 I have replaced bios and checked SPI traces. Not sure about USB activity but the mouse light comes on.

title: 820 00165 No VCORE
message:
Check diode mode to ground at 3V3_S0.
Post P3V3S0_EN level.

title: 820 00165 No VCORE
message:
PP3V3_S0 is there it probably always was but I probably checked it after checking CPUVR_PGOOD_R which shuts down the machine. If I had the fan connected I would have realized.

Diode PP3V3_S0 = 0.36

Diode P3V3S0_EN = 0.64

Voltage = 3.3

CPU stuffed?

title: 820 00165 No VCORE
message:
Check CPU_VCCST_PWRGD.
Do you get voltage at L7310/20?

title: 820 00165 No VCORE
message:
VCCST power good is required, before enabling VCORE.
Post U1930 voltages.

title: 820 00165 No VCORE
message:
Check R1931.
If good, change U1930.

title: 820 00165 No VCORE
message: Thanks for sorting that out. It was U1930
